# AI-Native SDLC is the contract

`.sdlc/sdlc.yaml` is the source of truth; read it before any non-trivial
change. Identify your `phase`, obey its `gates`, and stamp every `.sdlc/`
artifact with `common_provenance`.

`AGENTS.md` is the session entry point — it lists, in order, the memories
to reload (`.sdlc/memories/*`) and the durable index (`.sdlc/INDEX.md`).
Reload those before acting.

Slash commands map to phases: `/intent` `/spec` `/adr`
`/implement` `/verify` `/review` `/release` `/incident` `/learn`
(see `.cursor/commands/`).

When in doubt, pause rather than violate a gate or ship without provenance.
